{
  "texts": [
    "Reghenzani et al. [83] introduce an innovative framework for run-time pWCET estimation and quality monitoring.",
    "This approach dynamically monitors application behaviors to trigger pWCET reestimations as necessary, thereby accommodating unforeseen application faults or deviations from offline estimations.",
    "Their method leverages the EVT to analyze execution time samples, ensuring that the pWCET estimates remain representative of the system's actual performance under varying conditions.",
    "ChallengesIn conclusion, the mentioned measurement-based and hybrid analysis techniques used in the aforementioned papers, similar to static analysis methods, require detailed knowledge of hardware and software, leading to the same challenges faced by static analysis techniques.MBDTA faces several significant challenges that affect its trustworthiness.",
    "The first challenge lies in test conditions."
  ]
}